article.headline: Houston 70, UAB 64
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Robert McKiver scored 18 points and Dion Dowell hit the go-ahead 3-pointer with 2:23 left as Houston beat UAB 70-64 on Saturday night. Jamar Thorpe scored 16 points and Oliver Lafayette added 11 points for Houston (14-11, 8-3 Conference USA), who beat UAB for the first time in five meetings. Wen Mukubu scored a game-high 24 points for the Blazers (13-13, 5-7). Paul Delaney III scored 13 points and Frank Holmes added 10. Dowell's go-ahead 3-pointer was his second from the same spot in as many possessions for the Cougars. He finished with 9 points, all on 3s. UAB led by eight at halftime after shooting 50 percent in the first half. But the Blazers shot just 31 percent in the second half, including hitting just 1 of 12 3-pointers.
